{"lemma":"مَن","slug":"مَن","root":"م.ن","root_slug":"م-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ن","pos":null,"pos_camel":"pron_rel","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَن","root":"","pos":"N","occurrence_count":871},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","prep","pron","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":29},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43716","n43717","n43720"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D9%86"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"prep","gloss":"having partitive effect: of, some of, parts of, one of","examples":[{"text":"أَكَلْتُ مِنَ الطَّعَامِ.","english":"I ate [some] of the food."},{"text":"أَلَيْسَ مِنْكُمْ رَجُلٌ رَشِيدٌ","english":"Is there not a right-minded man among you?"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"made of","examples":[{"text":"تِمْثَالٌ مِنَ ٱلرُّخَامِ","english":"a statue of marble"},{"text":"خَاتَمٌ مِنْ ذَهَبٍ","english":"a ring of gold, a gold ring"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"containing, including","examples":[{"text":"كُوبٌ مِنَ ٱلْقَهْوَةِ","english":"a cup of coffee"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"pertaining to"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"to wit"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"from, away from, out of"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"at, on"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"in relation to, with respect to"},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"due to, owing to","examples":[{"text":"مَاتَ مِنَ ٱلْعَطَشِ","english":"He died of thirst."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"between; in contrast with","examples":[{"text":"تَمَكَّنُوا مِنْهُ","english":"They took power over him."},{"text":"مَيَّزَ الْجَيِّدَ مِنَ ٱلرَّدِيءِ","english":"He differentiated/discerned between the good and the bad"}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"than (with comparatives)","examples":[{"text":"مَالِي أَكْثَرُ مِنْ مَالِكَ / أَنَا أَكْثَرُ مِنْكَ مَالاً","english":"I have more money than you."}]},{"pos":"prep","gloss":"any (as a subject or object)","examples":[{"text":"مَا رَآنِي مِنْ أَحَدٍ.","english":"No one saw me."},{"text":"مَا رَأَيْتُ مِنْ أَحَدٍ.","english":"I saw no one."}]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"who?","tags":["interrogative"]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"which?, which one?","tags":["interrogative"]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"who, the one who, he who, those who, everyone who","tags":["relative"]},{"pos":"pron","gloss":"whoever","tags":["conditional"],"examples":[{"text":"مَنْ جَدَّ وَجَدَ","english":"seek and ye shall find"},{"text":"فَمَنْ يَعْمَلْ مِثْقَالَ ذَرَّةٍ خَيْرًا يَرَهُ\nوَمَنْ يَعْمَلْ مِثْقَالَ ذَرَّةٍ شَرًّا يَرَهُ","english":"So whoever does an atom's weight of good will see it,\n And whoever does an atom's weight of evil will see it."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be kind, kindly, benign, gracious, benevolent (عَلَى (ʕalā))"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to show, to grant, to confer (عَلَى (ʕalā))","examples":[{"text":"إن المسلمين يعرفون المهارات القيادية المختلفة التي مَنَّ بها الله على نبيّه الكريم.","english":"Muslims know the different leadership skills that God has bestowed upon His noble Prophet."}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to cut off, to curtail","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to jade, to tire","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to decrease, to diminish, to reduce","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to reproach, to upbraid","examples":[{"text":"وَتِلْكَ نِعْمَةٌ تَمُنُّهَا عَلَيَّ أَنْ عَبَّدْتَ بَنِي إِسْرَائِيلَ","english":"And this is the past favour wherewith thou reproachest me: that thou hast enslaved the Children of Israel."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَنَّ (manna) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"favor, benefit, blessing, boon"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gracious bestowal, gift, largess"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"manna","examples":[{"text":"يَا بَنِي إِسْرَاءِيلَ قَدْ أَنْجَيْنٰكُمْ مِنْ عَدُوِّكُمْ وَوٰعَدْنٰكُمْ جَانِبَ ٱلطُّورِ ٱلْأَيْمَنَ وَنَزَّلْنَا عَلَيْكُمُ ٱلْمَنَّ وَٱلسَّلْوَى","english":"O sons of Israel, We did deliver you from your enemy and We did covenant with you on the right side of the Mount [Sinai] and We did send down unto you the manna and the quails."},{"text":"وَأَكَلَ بَنُو إِسْرَاءِيلَ ٱلْمَنَّ أَرْبَعِينَ سَنَةً حَتَّى جَاءُوا إِلَى أَرْضٍ عَامِرَةٍ.","english":"And the sons of Israel have eaten the manna [for] forty years, until their coming to the land to be inhabited."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a sweet liquid substance such as honey, nectar, or manna; honeydew","tags":["countable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"aphid","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a historical unit of mass – translatable as mina or maund – varying usually between ca. 1–3 kilograms, however in some cases also going up over 40 kilograms."}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Proto-West Semitic *min. Cognate with Hebrew מִן (min).\n\nFrom Proto-Semitic *mann-. Cognates include Aramaic מן (man), Ge'ez መኑ (männu) and Amharic ማን (man).\n\nThe noun is modelled on a large scale upon Aramaic מַנָּא / ܡܢܐ (mannā) from the same root.\n\nFrom Aramaic מָנָא (mānā), from Akkadian 𒈠𒉡𒌑 (manû), whence also Sumerian 𒈠𒈾 (ma-na /⁠mana⁠/) and Hebrew מָנֶה (mānḗ)."},"ipa":["/min/","/man/","/mann/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43716","headword_ar":"مَنْ","root":"mn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[used for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What?"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in the following of El-Khansà,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"A^alaA mano liEayoniY laA tajif~u dumuwEuhaA"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O! what aileth mine eye, that its tears dry not?"},{"kind":"text","text":"quoted in the TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fvA^","text_ar":"فثا"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano","text_ar":"مَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":": respecting its dual"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manaAno","text_ar":"مَنَانْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manayono","text_ar":"مَنَيْنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and its pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manuwno","text_ar":"مَنُونْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maniyno","text_ar":"مَنِينْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", see I'Ak, p. 319. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano liY bika*aA","text_ar":"مَنْ لِى بِكَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi","text_ar":"بِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(near the end of the paragraph)."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n43717","headword_ar":"مِنْ","root":"mn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zayodN A^aEoqalu mino A^ano yako*ib","text_ar":"زَيْدٌ اَعْقَلُ مِنْ اَنْ يَكْذِب"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina","text_ar":"مِنَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al*~aiY yako*ibu","text_ar":"الذَِّى يَكْذِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kull, p. 78) [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is more reasonable than he who lies:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but, though this is the virtual meaning, the proper explanation, accord. to modern usage, is, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano","text_ar":"اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is here for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a","text_ar":"اَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"with the adjunct pronoun"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hu","text_ar":"هُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for in a phrase of this kind, an adjunct pronoun is sometimes expressed; so that the aor. must be marfooa; and the literal meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is more reasonable than that he will lie;"},{"kind":"text","text":"which is equivalent to saying,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd is too reasonable to lie."},{"kind":"text","text":"It may be doubted, however, whether a phrase of this kind be of classical authority. The only other instance that I have found is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa A^aHoSanu mino A^ano yoraAm waA^aEaz~u","text_ar":"هُوَ اَحْصَنُ مِنْ اَنْ يْرَام وَاَعَزُّ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"min A^ano yuDaAm","text_ar":"مِن اَنْ يُضَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^alo","text_ar":"اَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Accord. to modern usage, one may say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anota A^aEoqalu mino","text_ar":"اَنْتَ اَعْقَلُ مِنْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~aka tafoEalu ka*aA","text_ar":"اَنَّكَ تَفْعَلُ كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", which virtually means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou art too reasonable to do such a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and here we cannot substitute"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A@l~a*in","text_ar":"ا@لَّذِن"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~","text_ar":"اَنّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano","text_ar":"اَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a","text_ar":"اَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axozaY A@ll~`hu AlkaA*iba min~iY waminoka","text_ar":"اَخْزَى ا@للّٰهُ الكَاذِبَ مِنِّى وَمِنْكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aY~N","text_ar":"اَىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytu minohu A^asadFA","text_ar":"لَقِيتُ مِنْهُ اَسَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^asodN","text_ar":"اَسْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laqiytu","text_ar":"لَقِيتُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"minohu","text_ar":"مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baHorFA","text_ar":"بَحْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu minohu baHorFA","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ مِنْهُ بَحْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bHr","text_ar":"بحر"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Einoda","text_ar":"عِنْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jad~N","text_ar":"جَدٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaraY minohu majoraY","text_ar":"جَرَى مِنْهُ مَجْرَى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka*aA","text_ar":"كَذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jrY","text_ar":"جرى"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", differences between: see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"often means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Some."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b10-  Often redundant: see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EyD","text_ar":"عيض"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b11-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Of,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"among:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see two exs. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY","text_ar":"فِى"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter part. ―         -b12-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HusayonN min~iY waA^anaA minohu","text_ar":"حُسَيْنٌ مِنِّى وَاَنَا مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hoseyn and I are as one thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as though each were a part of the other,] in respect of the love that is due to us, &c. (Commencement of a tradition in the Jámi' es-Sagheer: thus explained in the Expos. of El-Munáwee.) See Ham, p. 139; and De Sacy's Gr. i. 492. ―         -b13-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA A^anaA mano dadK walaA Ald~adu min~iY","text_ar":"مَا اَنَا مَنْ دَدٍ وَلَا الدَّدُ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dd","text_ar":"دد"},{"kind":"text","text":". IbrD confirms my rendering of this saying. ―         -b14-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yataEar~aDu A_ilaY $aYo'K layosa minohu","text_ar":"يَتَعَرَّضُ اـِلَى شَىْءٍ لَيْسَ مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He applies himself to a thing not of his business to do"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E$","text_ar":"عش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b15-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa min~aA","text_ar":"لَيْسَ مِنَّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is not of our dispositions, nor of our way, course,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner, of acting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"g$","text_ar":"غش"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b16-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa min~iY","text_ar":"لَيْسَ مِنِّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kur, ii. 250)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is not of my followers:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he is not at one,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in union, with me."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd. See 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TEm","text_ar":"طعم"},{"kind":"text","text":".) See a similar usage of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mn","text_ar":"من"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiySN","text_ar":"عِيصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b17-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anaA minohu kaHaAqini AlA_ihaAlapi","text_ar":"اَنَا مِنْهُ كَحَاقِنِ الاـِهَالَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaAqinN","text_ar":"حَاقِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b18-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino","text_ar":"مِنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used in the sense of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY","text_ar":"فى"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino yawomi AljumoEapi","text_ar":"مِنْ يَوْمِ الجُمْعَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on, the day of congregation"},{"kind":"text","text":"] in the Kur lxii. 9. (K, Jel.) So, too, in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino yawomihi","text_ar":"مِنْ يَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on, his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same,"},{"kind":"text","text":"day: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino saAEatihi","text_ar":"مِنْ سَاعَتِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"In,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"at, his,"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the same, instant of time."},{"kind":"text","text":"See also De Sacy's Gr., ii. 526."}],"source_refs":["Bd","Jel"]},{"entry_id":"n43720","headword_ar":"مَنٌّ","root":"mn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riTolN","text_ar":"رِطْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}